We are trying to remove fatmgrid. And it's removed from the model and it's OK. But, several CLM tools depend on it, so in the short run it's better to put it back in the XML database, and remove it from the tools later. so fatmgrid remains deprecated, but I'm going to keep it around for a bit longer.

The following tools depend on it...

mkmapgrids
mksurfdata_map
aerd/ndep regrid.ncl
ndeplintInterp.ncl

mkmapgrids/mkmapgrids.csh:set query="$query -justvalue -csmdata $CSMDATA -var fatmgrid "
mksurfdata_map/mksurfdata.pl:         $griddata = `$scrdir/../../bld/queryDefaultNamelist.pl $queryfilopts $usrnam -var fatmgrid`;
ncl_scripts/aerdepregrid.ncl:  gridinfile  = systemfunc( querynml+" -res "+resin+" -var fatmgrid" );
ncl_scripts/aerdepregrid.ncl:     gridfile    = systemfunc( querynml+" -res "+res  +" -var fatmgrid" );
ncl_scripts/ndeplintInterp.ncl:   filetype  = "fatmgrid";
ncl_scripts/ndeplintInterp.ncl:   area = dble2flt( ncg->$vname$ ) * 1000000.0 ;  Area in m^2 from fatmgrid file which has it in kg^2
ncl_scripts/ndepregrid.ncl:  gridinfile  = systemfunc( querynml+" -res "+resin+" -var fatmgrid" );
ncl_scripts/ndepregrid.ncl:     gridfile    = systemfunc( querynml+" -res "+res  +" -var fatmgrid" );


These can all be changed to use mapping, surf, or domain files for the same information.

After running create_clone followed by configure -case, the paths used by CLM's build-namelist tool point to the cloned case; they should point to the new case directory.

For example, I cloned a case named test_diags_1014_clm4_0_37, to make a new case test_diags_1017. Here are the paths as documented in clm.buildnml.csh:


#! lnd_in:: Comment:
#! This namelist was created using the following command-line:
#!     /glade/proj3/cseg/people/sacks/cesm_code/clm_landice_diagnostics2/models/lnd/clm/bld/build-namelist -config /glade/proj3/cseg/people/sacks/cesm_tests/test_diags_1014_clm4_0_37/Buildconf/clmconf/config_cache.xml -res 1.9x2.5 
-mask gx1v6 -ignore_ic_year -use_case 2000_glacierMEC_control -infile cesm_namelist -clm_start_type default -rtm_res R05 -rtm_tstep 10800 -co2_ppmv 367.0 -datm_presaero clim_2000 -glc_grid gland20 -namelist &clm_inparm  / -csmdata 
$DIN_LOC_ROOT -inputdata /glade/proj3/cseg/people/sacks/cesm_tests/test_diags_1014_clm4_0_37/Buildconf/clm.input_data_list
